The article announces several nominations and appointments for the Federal Trade Commission (FTC). Rohit Chopra is nominated to be a Federal Trade Commissioner for the unexpired term of seven years, replacing Joshua D. Wright who resigned. Noah Joshua Phillips is nominated to be a Federal Trade Commissioner for a term of seven years, replacing Julie Simone Brill whose term has expired. Joseph Simons is nominated to be a Federal Trade Commissioner for a term of seven years, replacing Terrell McSweeny whose term has expired. Christine S. Wilson is nominated to be a Federal Trade Commissioner for the unexpired term of seven years, replacing Maureen K. Ohlhausen. Additionally, Christine S. Wilson is also nominated for reappointment as a Federal Trade Commissioner for a term of seven years starting from September 26, 2018.